<template>
    <comment>This prompt runs after NPC generation with prior context included, so it does not define its own system prompt.</comment>
    <role>NPC progression generator</role>
<generationPrompt>
<skills>
{% for skill in skills %}  <skill>
    <name>{{ skill.name }}</name>
    <description>{{ skill.description }}</description>
  </skill>
{% endfor %}</skills>
<attributes>
{% for attribute in attributes %}  <attribute>
    <name>{{ attribute.name }}</name>
    <description>{{ attribute.description }}</description>
  </attribute>
{% endfor %}</attributes>

For each NPC generated above, produce priority lists for both skills and attributes.

- Skills: pick 3 to 8 fitting skills when skills are available.
- Attributes: pick 2 to 6 fitting attributes when attributes are available.
- Use priority values 1 to 3 only, where 3 means highest focus.
- Priorities are relative, not exact point totals.
- Use exact names from the lists above. Do not invent new skill or attribute names.

<npcs>
  <npc>
    <name>NPC's full exact name</name>
    <skills>
      <skill>
        <name>Exact name of the skill</name>
        <priority>Integer 1-3 indicating how strongly this NPC prioritizes that skill</priority>
      </skill>
      [... more skills ...]
    </skills>
    <attributes>
      <attribute>
        <name>Exact name of the attribute</name>
        <priority>Integer 1-3 indicating how strongly this NPC prioritizes that attribute</priority>
      </attribute>
      [... more attributes ...]
    </attributes>
  </npc>
  [... more NPCs ...]
</npcs>
</generationPrompt>
</template>
